        </p>
        <p>
          Caravaggio, the painter whose dramatic use of light and shadow revolutionized Western art, killed Ranuccio Tomassoni in a street fight near the Campo Marzio in 1606. The exact location‚Äînear the modern Via della Pallacorda‚Äîis included on tours that trace Caravaggio's violent life through Rome's streets. His paintings, many of which depict death with unflinching realism, hang in churches throughout the city where they were originally commissioned.
        </p>
      </div>
